# `.dockerignore` lives at the *build context* root. The playground's
# Dockerfile sits at playground/deploy/Dockerfile, but its build
# context is the repo root (set by playground/deploy/deploy.sh's
# `(cd "$REPO_ROOT" && fly deploy …)` wrapper) so the Dockerfile's
# `COPY rustviz2-plugin/` etc. paths resolve. Without this file,
# the deploy context would slurp multi-GiB target/ + node_modules/
# trees on every build.

**/target/
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/build/

.git/
.github/
.vscode/

# Generated mdbook output (per-build, not source)
mdbook-rustviz/test-book/book/

# Frontend caches
**/.parcel-cache/
**/.vite/
**/.tsbuildinfo
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# OS / editor noise
**/.DS_Store
**/*.swp
